Diagnostic description. Body length 15.9 –19.0 mm (19.0 mm in the lectotype of
Eusilpha gilleti
), maximum body width 8.9 –11.0 mm (11.0 mm in the lectotype ). Pronotum orange in dorsal view, with large, well-delimited, metallic black medial spot on disc (
Figs. 9–10
). Hypomeron medially dark metallic blue in ventral view. Elytra with green metallic luster; outline widely subrectangular; costae very robust and distinctly elevated (
Figs. 9–10
).

Male . Metatibia distinctly bent. Male genital segment with longer spiculum gastrale in ventral view (
Fig. 51
). Aedeagus with median lobe only slightly shorter than short, slender parameres (
Fig. 50
).

Female . Genital segment with tergum 10 small, hexagonal in shape in dorsal view (
Fig. 52
).
